<refsect1 id="libfprint-2-Logging.description" role="desc">
<title role="desc.title">Description</title>
<para>Logging in libfprint is handled through GLib's logging system, and behave the same
way as in the GLib <ulink url="https://developer.gnome.org/glib/stable/glib-Message-Logging.html">Message Output and Debugging Functions</ulink>
documentation.</para>
<para>You should include <literal>fpi-log.h</literal> as early as possible in your sources, just after
setting the <literal>FP_COMPONENT</literal> define to a string unique to your sources. This will
set the suffix of the <literal>G_LOG_DOMAIN</literal> used for printing.</para>

</refsect1>
<refsect1 id="libfprint-2-Logging.functions_details" role="details">
<title role="details.title">Functions</title>
<refsect2 id="BUG-ON:CAPS" role="macro">
<title>BUG_ON()</title>
<indexterm zone="BUG-ON:CAPS"><primary>BUG_ON</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting language="C">#define             BUG_ON(condition)</programlisting>
<para>Uses <link linkend="fp-err"><function>fp_err()</function></link> to print an error if the <parameter>condition</parameter>
 is true.</para>
<refsect3 id="BUG-ON.parameters" role="parameters">
<title>Parameters</title>
<informaltable role="parameters_table" pgwide="1" frame="none">
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="parameters_name" colwidth="150px"/>
<colspec colname="parameters_description"/>
<colspec colname="parameters_annotations" colwidth="200px"/>
<tbody>
<row><entry role="parameter_name"><para>condition</para></entry>
<entry role="parameter_description"><para>the condition to check</para></entry>
<entry role="parameter_annotations"></entry></row>
</tbody></tgroup></informaltable>
</refsect3></refsect2>
<refsect2 id="BUG:CAPS" role="macro">
<title>BUG</title>
<indexterm zone="BUG:CAPS"><primary>BUG</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting language="C">#define BUG() BUG_ON (1)
</programlisting>
<para>Same as <link linkend="BUG-ON:CAPS"><function>BUG_ON()</function></link> but is always true.</para>
</refsect2>

</refsect1>
